    'reduction.tutorialTitle': 'ENTROPY FIELD // COMPRESSION',
    'reduction.tutorialMessage': '“The seven-layer matrix carries too much raw information, so I added Entropy-Field Compression to your terminal. Once you know an unopened cell is a mine, remove it directly from the matrix; its position and every affected clue will recalculate the remaining mine counts.”',
    'reduction.tutorialFact': 'DESKTOP: press both mouse buttons on the target cell. MOBILE: double-tap any unopened cell, including a flagged one, in either Dig or Flag Mode. A wrong deduction triggers failure; after success, affected clues update automatically and any zero recursively opens its safe region.',
