    'tutorial.neighborsTitle': 'Define neighboring cells',
    'tutorial.neighbors': 'This ruleset treats every other cube in the three 3×3 layers around a target as adjacent: 9 above, 8 on the same layer, and 9 below. Each coordinate is counted once. The number shows how many actual mines occupy those positions.',
    'tutorial.neighborsFact': 'The theoretical maximum number is 26. The beginner board has only 3 mines, so its displayed numbers range from 0–3.',
    'tutorial.guidedTitle': 'Hands-on Sequence: Dig Mode',
    'tutorial.guided': '“Time for the live run. Left-click digs on desktop; on mobile, select Dig in the bottom dock and tap. The cyan frame marks this step’s safe cube. Each time you finish a move, I’ll automatically deduce and mark the next one.”',
    'tutorial.guided.mouse': '“Time for the live run. Left-click digs. The cyan frame marks this step’s safe cube. Each time you finish a move, I’ll automatically deduce and mark the next one.”',
    'tutorial.guided.touch': '“Time for the live run. Select Dig in the bottom dock, then tap the cyan target. The cyan frame marks this step’s safe cube. Each time you finish a move, I’ll automatically deduce and mark the next one.”',
    'tutorial.guidedFact': 'The training matrix is randomly selected from layouts that are logically solvable from start to finish. The first move is protected; every later conclusion uses only visible clues and current flags—no peeking and no guessing.',
    'tutorial.followMe': 'Start Step One',
    'tutorial.flagModeTitle': 'New Move: Flag Mode',
    'tutorial.flagMode': '“Now learn flags. On desktop, right-click places a flag and left-click still only digs. On mobile, select Flag in the bottom dock, then tap the magenta target.”',
    'tutorial.flagMode.mouse': '“Now learn flags. Right-click places a flag, while left-click still only digs. Flag the magenta target.”',
    'tutorial.flagMode.touch': '“Now learn flags. Select Flag in the bottom dock, then tap the magenta target. Switch back to Dig when you want to reveal cubes again.”',
    'tutorial.flagModeFact': 'Cyan means safe to dig, magenta means a proven mine, and gold frames mark the number clues used by the current deduction. I’ll explain every conclusion.',
    'tutorial.tryFlag': 'Deduce and Flag',
    'tutorial.guided.step': 'Step {step} |',
    'tutorial.guided.hint.protectedStart': 'Step {step}/{total} | Dig: the first move is protected, so X{x}/Y{y}/Z{z} is confirmed safe. Left-click on desktop or tap the cyan target on mobile to reveal the number clues.',
